-- Turkey Stocks: Acibadem, Akbank, Sabanci Holding Are Active
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-03-26T15:09:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/turkey-stocks-acibadem-akbank-sabanci-holding-are-active.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  surged 1.9 percent to 62,561.47, ending four days of
losses and extending its gain this year to 22 percent, heading
for the best quarter since 2010.  The following stocks were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Acibadem Saglik Hizmetleri & Ticaret AS (ACIBD)  , a chain
of hospitals, slumped 0.8 percent to 25 liras after owner
 Khazanah Nasional Bhd (KNBZ) . of  Malaysia  said it would offer to buy
minority shares at $13.67 per share, compared with the dollar-
converted closing price of about $13.83 per share on March 23.  Akbank TAS (AKBNK)  , Turkey’s second-largest listed
lender by market value, led declines on the stock exchange,
losing 3.3 percent to 7.02 liras after  Citigroup Inc. (C)  said it
would cut its 20 percent stake in the Turkish lender by at least
half.  Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL)  , Turkey’s second-
biggest group of companies and owner of 49 percent of Akbank
TAS, gained 0.5 percent to 7.62 liras after falling as much as
2.1 percent in intraday trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
